message.text:
It is very "Sunny" today in Tokyo! 
In May, there is a weather term "Satsukibare/Gogatsubare"(五月晴れ: literally, sunny spells in May）.

It originally means "sunny spells during rainy season", but, in recent years, it is more popular to use for a clear sky in the early May. After the long holiday (Golden Week), our mind is not cleared up like today's blue sky...How is the weather in your area?
今日の東京は「五月晴れ」！日本はゴールデンウィークが終わったばかりでまだまだ心は晴れません・・・
http://words.marugotoweb.jp/search_detail.php?id=1753&p=1&q=天気&source=search&lang=en

message.text:
ATTENTION to the MANGA creators all over the world!
The 8th International MANGA Award
第8回国際漫画賞の作品募集中！
Try&compete your MANGA skills and win a MANGA trip ticket to Japan!
For more info: http://www.manga-award.jp

Looking for MANGA creators who would contribute to spread MANGA culture overseas and international cultural exchange through MANGA! 
Award recipients will be invited to Japan by the Japan
Foundation for the award ceremony, exchange opinions with Japanese
MANGA creators etc.
Apply now!　Deadline: May 31st, 2014.
第8回国際漫画賞で海外からの漫画作品が集う！
受賞者は、国際交流基金の招きで授賞式に合わせて来日し、日本の漫画家との意見交換など漫画文化の発信地である日本を体感してもらいます。
